<collectingCountry id="DBEB1BB3FFEBFFC3FBF3BFBCFAC7FC58" box="[1026,1326,898,922]" name="South Africa" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Republic of South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="613895C1FFEBFFC3FACCBFBCFEE8FC78" country="South Africa" name="Eastern Cape" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Eastern Cape</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613895C1FFEBFFC3FEFABF9CFE64FC78" box="[267,397,930,954]" country="South Africa" name="Free State" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Free State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613895C1FFEBFFC3FE66BF9CFDEAFC78" box="[407,515,930,954]" country="South Africa" name="Gauteng" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Gauteng</collectingRegion>
, KwaZulu/Natal, 
<collectingRegion id="613895C1FFEBFFC3FD29BF9CFC78FC78" box="[728,913,930,954]" country="South Africa" name="Northern Cape" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Northern Cape</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613895C1FFEBFFC3FC6ABF9CFBC2FC7B" box="[923,1067,930,954]" country="South Africa" name="North West" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">North West</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion id="613895C1FFEBFFC3FB99BF9CFAFAFC78" box="[1128,1299,930,954]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Western Cape</collectingRegion>
Provinces), 
<collectingCountry id="DBEB1BB3FFEBFFC3FF31BFFCFEC9FC18" box="[192,288,962,986]" name="Zambia" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Zambia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="DBEB1BB3FFEBFFC3FEDDBFFCFE46FC18" box="[300,431,962,986]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
. For a list of collecting localities see 
<bibRefCitation id="C76D26D2FFEBFFC3FC9FBFFCFB4CFC18" author="Basilewsky, P." box="[878,1189,962,986]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky (1977: 80-87)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A3435B23FFEBFFC3FF31B83FFD37F978" blockId="6.[192,1440,1025,1850]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FF31B83FFE5EFBD8" bold="true" box="[192,439,1025,1050]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Taxonomic Notes.</emphasis>
The names listed above in synonymy (as well as many of the taxa listed under 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FA75B83CFED2FBF8" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wahlbergi">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FA75B83CFED2FBF8" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. wahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below) were generally considered valid species before 
<bibRefCitation id="C76D26D2FFEBFFC3FC10B81CFB76FBF8" author="Burgeon, L." box="[993,1183,1058,1082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="273 - 351" refId="ref7492" refString="Burgeon, L. 1929. Monographie du genre Graphipterus Latr. Annales de la Societe Entomologique du Belgique 69: 273 - 351." type="journal article" year="1929">Burgeon (1929)</bibRefCitation>
placed them as subspecies under 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FE9EB87CFE1FFB98" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[367,502,1090,1114]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FE9EB87CFE1FFB98" box="[367,502,1090,1114]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. cordiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="C76D26D2FFEBFFC3FDF4B87CFD0CFB98" author="Basilewsky, P." box="[517,741,1090,1114]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky (1977)</bibRefCitation>
treated all of the names that I have included here under the species 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FEBCB85CFE3DFBB8" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[333,468,1122,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FEBCB85CFE3DFBB8" box="[333,468,1122,1146]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. cordiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FDE1B85CFD46FBB8" box="[528,687,1122,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wahlbergi">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FDE1B85CFD46FBB8" box="[528,687,1122,1146]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. wahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as subspecies of a single polytypic species, which he called 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FA75B85CFECDFB58" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FA75B85CFECDFB58" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. cordiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by priority. This approach is problematic, as there are clear areas of overlap between many of the alleged subspecific forms (e.g. between 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FD3EB89CFC65FB78" box="[719,908,1186,1210]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. c. betshuana</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FC38B89CFB74FB78" box="[969,1181,1186,1210]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. c. subhamatus</emphasis>
, between 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FAE8B89CFF16FB1B" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. c. betshuana</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FECCB8FCFDF3FB18" box="[317,538,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FE8AB8FCFDF3FB18" authorityName="Peringuey" authorityYear="1892" box="[379,538,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zambezianus">zambezianus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and between 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FD3CB8FCFC9EFB18" box="[717,887,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FCFAB8FCFC9EFB18" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1848" box="[779,887,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatus">hamatus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FC44B8FCFB9EFB18" box="[949,1143,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FC02B8FCFB9EFB18" authorityName="Peringuey" authorityYear="1896" box="[1011,1143,1218,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transfugus">transfugus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
), and these overlapping populations generally lack intergrade forms (
<bibRefCitation id="C76D26D2FFEBFFC3FD17B8DCFC51FB38" author="Basilewsky, P." box="[742,952,1250,1274]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky 1977</bibRefCitation>
). Furthermore, several pairs of putative subspecies (
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FEA2B93CFE1FFAD8" box="[339,502,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FE63B93CFE1FFAD8" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[402,502,1282,1306]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">cordiger</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FDC4B93CFCEAFAD8" box="[565,771,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. c. subcordiger</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FCE3B93CFC57FAD8" box="[786,958,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FCA3B93CFC57FAD8" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1848" box="[850,958,1282,1306]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatus">hamatus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FC0DB93CFB3BFAD8" box="[1020,1234,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. c. subhamatus</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FB10B93CFA49FAD8" box="[1249,1440,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. c. betshuana</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FF04B91CFE45FAF8" box="[245,428,1314,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cordiger" subSpecies="wahlbergi">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FF04B91CFE45FAF8" box="[245,428,1314,1338]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. c. wahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) have identical patterns of elytral pubescence and can be separated only by collecting locality (
<bibRefCitation id="C76D26D2FFEBFFC3FEAAB97CFDC6FA98" author="Basilewsky, P." box="[347,559,1346,1370]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky 1977</bibRefCitation>
). Having examined extensive collections of this species in the museum collections listed above, I came to the conclusion that at least two separate species are present. One species has a large rounded patch of dark pubescence on the elytra, and a triangular projection on disc associated with the basal band of light pubescence. The other species has a more transverse, often rectangular band of dark pubescence on the elytra, and consistently lacks the triangular projection from the basal band of light pubescence. By priority, these two species are named 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FBC9B9DCFB56FA38" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[1080,1215,1506,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FBC9B9DCFB56FA38" box="[1080,1215,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. cordiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FB0AB9DCFA70FA38" box="[1275,1433,1506,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wahlbergi">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FB0AB9DCFA70FA38" box="[1275,1433,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. wahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, respectively. Recognition of two separate species resolves the problems associated with overlapping subspecies, since the observed areas of overlap are always between forms with a rounded patch of dark pubescence and forms with a transverse band of dark pubescence. The subspecific taxa with identical markings can be interpreted as disjunct populations of either 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FC4ABA5CFBAAF9B8" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[955,1091,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FC4ABA5CFBAAF9B8" box="[955,1091,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. cordiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the case of 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FB0CBA5CFA49F9B8" box="[1277,1440,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FACDBA5CFA49F9B8" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[1340,1440,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">cordiger</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FF06BABCFE2FF958" box="[247,454,1666,1690]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. c. subcordiger</emphasis>
and in the case of 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FD40BABCFCB4F958" box="[689,861,1666,1690]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
G. c. 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FD00BABCFCB4F958" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1848" box="[753,861,1666,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatus">hamatus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FC6CBABCFB9DF958" box="[925,1140,1666,1690]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. c. subhamatus</emphasis>
) or 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FB57BABCFAAFF958" box="[1190,1350,1666,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wahlbergi">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FB57BABCFAAFF958" box="[1190,1350,1666,1690]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. wahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the case of 
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FEE8BA9CFE3EF978" box="[281,471,1698,1722]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. c. betshuana</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FDE5BA9CFD24F978" box="[532,717,1698,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="cordiger" subSpecies="wahlbergi">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FDE5BA9CFD24F978" box="[532,717,1698,1722]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">G. c. wahlbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A3435B23FFEBFFC3FF01BAFCFDC6F8F8" blockId="6.[192,1440,1025,1850]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName id="64FC20A0FFEBFFC3FF01BAFCFDECF918" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[240,517,1730,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Graphipterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordiger">
<emphasis id="91888731FFEBFFC3FF01BAFCFDECF918" box="[240,517,1730,1754]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Graphipterus cordiger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as restricted here is generally distributed throughout the southern and central provinces of the 
<collectingCountry id="DBEB1BB3FFEBFFC3FE00BADCFCCEF938" box="[497,807,1762,1786]" name="South Africa" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Republic of South Africa</collectingCountry>
, with populations also in central 
<collectingCountry id="DBEB1BB3FFEBFFC3FB3CBADCFAD2F938" box="[1229,1339,1762,1786]" name="Namibia" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Namibia</collectingCountry>
, central 
<collectingCountry id="DBEB1BB3FFEBFFC3FF31BB3CFEABF8D8" box="[192,322,1794,1818]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry id="DBEB1BB3FFEBFFC3FE30BB3CFDC8F8D8" box="[449,545,1794,1818]" name="Zambia" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Zambia</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry id="DBEB1BB3FFEBFFC3FD51BB3CFCA8F8D8" box="[672,833,1794,1818]" name="Mozambique" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="DBEB1BB3FFEBFFC3FC71BB3CFC09F8D8" box="[896,992,1794,1818]" name="Malawi" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Malawi</collectingCountry>
. For a full synonymy for this species, see 
<bibRefCitation id="C76D26D2FFEBFFC3FF1FBB1CFDC2F8F8" author="Basilewsky, P." box="[238,555,1826,1850]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 472" refId="ref7374" refString="Basilewsky, P. 1977. Revision du genre Graphipterus Latreille (Coleoptera Carabidae). Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Annales, Serie in- 8 o, Sciences Zoologiques 221: 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1977">Basilewsky (1977: 76–77)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
